message: Always use the growth serum once on two different animals. message: Focus on identifying the two largest animals in your inventory. Use the 'growth serum' exactly once on each of these two animals. Then, combine these two 'grown' animals. message: To maximize your score, always use a 'growth serum' once on two different animals. Do NOT use it twice on the same animal, or use the 'mutation catalyst', as both will result in negative values. Aim to combine the two largest 'grown' animals possible. message: To maximize your score, use the growth serum only once on two different animals. Prioritize making the two largest possible animals 'grown'. If those two grown animals live in different environments (land+air, air+water, or land+water), combining them will give you an extra 5 points beyond their sum. If they live in the same environment, you will still get their sum, which is usually the next best outcome. Avoid using growth serum twice on one animal or using the mutation catalyst, as both lead to negative scores.

message: Welcome, future crafter! Here's what I learned: Growth serum adds value to an animal (large=+15, medium=+10, small=+5) and makes it 'grown'. Use growth serum only once per animal; using it twice or using mutation catalyst will make an animal's score negative. The best strategy is to use growth serum on two different 'large' animals, ideally with different habitats (land, water, air), then combine them for a +5 hybrid bonus (e.g., grown land animal + grown water animal = 15+15+5 = 35). Prioritize large animals if you only have one serum. Good luck!

message: To maximize your score, always use 'growth serum' exactly once on two different animals. Never use 'mutation catalyst' or 'growth serum' twice on the same animal, as it leads to negative scores. Grown animals gain value based on their initial size (large: 15, medium: 10, small: 5). After growing two animals, combine them. You will get an additional 5 points if the two combined animals lived in different habitats (land, water, or air). Aim to combine two grown animals that will give the highest total value, considering both their individual grown values and the potential +5 habitat bonus.
